---

Then create the topic:

```bash id="42c3sv"
/opt/kafka/bin/kafka-topics.sh \
--create \
--topic orders \
--bootstrap-server localhost:9092 \
--partitions 3 \
--replication-factor 1
```

---

# Why 3 Partitions?

Interview perspective:

If we create:

```text id="phag4u"
orders
Partitions = 3
```

Later:

```text id="xk6tmy"
Consumer A
Consumer B
Consumer C
```

can process data in parallel.

If we create:

```text id="20x7w0"
Partitions = 1
```

we lose parallelism.

